<h1>But This Breaks Websites - Won't I Get in Trouble?</h1>
<p>Fear not, this doesn't have any permanent effect on the website on which you play it, all the effects are just temporarily created by (huge and confusing strings) of JavaScript code that goes away as soon as you leave the page. So go nuts. If anything you're helping the other websites, as a link to all the sites that get played will appear on this site, and that's called SEO or SEF or SEM or link-farming or social-netowrking or something, and everybody loves that shit.</p>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Score</th>
      <th>Winning Element</th>
      <th>Losing Element</th>
      <th>Content</th>
      <th>URL</th>
      <th>Page</th>
    </tr>

  </thead>

  <tbody>
    <% @battles.each do |battle| %>
      <tr class="<%= cycle('even', 'odd') -%>">
        <td><%= battle.score %></td>
        <td><%= battle.winner.element %></td>
        <td>
          <% battle.winner.conquests.each do |conquest| %>
            <%= conquest.element %>
          <% end %>
        </td>
        <td><%= battle.winner.content %></td>
        <td><a href="<%= battle.winner.page.url %>" target="_blank"><%= battle.winner.page.url %></a></td>
        <td><%= battle.winner.page.title %></td>
      </tr>

    <% end %>
  </tbody>

</table>

